<br>
I am expecting the idol of thorned, shroud of nature, earring of essence and stone of morid to stop dropping (I think the guantlets of potence already stopped dropping). So I am there as often as possible trying as hard as possible to get them. And I hope that the angry goblin spawns a lot more often than every 5 days.<br>
<br>
Example of doing upgrades correctly: Chardok. Epic mobs and drops did not break, or if they did, were fixed quickly.<br>
<br>
Example of doing it wrong: Befallen. So much was broken, it is back to the old befallen.<br>
<br>
Example of doing it partly correct: upgrade of runneyeye. HQ <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> pieces</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> of ore (the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> stacking kind</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> which is used only to make the halfling sewing kit) stopped dropping for about 6-8 months. And since it dropped from a previously common mob, whose spawn became a single mob, only halfling tailors noticed the failure. And until the fan faire in Orlando, all the HQ pieces in the game were harvested before the upgrade.<br>
<br>
PS. don't reply to this claiming that HQ ore drops in other dungeons. I know that the non-stacking bricks of ore do indeed drop from any old word dungeon with goblins (with the exception of runnyeye). The PIECES (the ones that stack) were used in exactly 1 recipe in the game and they came from ONLY one mob: the goblin janitor. Who had a broken loot table for 6-8 months. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uangelsyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Angelsyn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://members.aol.com/karenwilder/icon_keyne.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(1/31/02 5:11:04 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3273.topic&index=206>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 3rd Chardok ring is shoulders/arms/wrist item (SOLVED)</span><hr size=1> Say...<br>
